The course provides an overview of the mid-19th-century Russian literature. Particular attention is given to creations by I. Turgenev, I. Gontšarov, A., Fet and Nekrassov. 
In depth will be addressed: the Turgenev's prose, poetry, and poems by Nekrassov written during the 1860s. In the seminars Turgenev's socio-psychological novels ("Home of the Gentry", "Fathers and Sons") are analyzed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim is to introduce the mid-19th century Russian literature and to provide a more detailed picture of the creations by I. Turgenev, I. Gontšarov, A., Fet and Nekrassov. To give a knowledge of the structural peculiarities of the mid-19th-century Russian social-psychological novel, to introduce the ideological and aesthetic orientation of the poetry during the period of 1840-1860.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Student who has passed the course: 
* has a systematic knowledge of the specificity of the development of the Russian literature during the mid-19th century;
* has a knowledge about the creations by Russian poets, playwrights, and prose writers of the mid-19th century.
* is able to bring out and analyze the specifics of the social-psychological novel of the mid-19th century; 
* is able to describe the aesthetic and ideological features of the poetry of the mid-19th century, i.e. the period of 1850s-1870.
